## Project Overview
{{.Description}}

## Tech Stack
- **Language**: Java 21
- **Framework**: Spring Boot 3.4
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17 (via Docker)
- **Build Tool**: Maven
- **ORM**: Spring Data JPA / Hibernate

## Project Structure
- `src/main/java/com/example/app/` - Application source code
- `src/main/java/com/example/app/controller/` - REST controllers
- `src/main/java/com/example/app/model/` - JPA entity classes
- `src/main/java/com/example/app/repository/` - Spring Data repositories
- `src/main/java/com/example/app/service/` - Business logic services
- `src/main/resources/` - Configuration files
- `src/test/java/` - Test classes
- `docs/supporting/` - Supporting documentation

## Development Commands
```bash
make start    # Start Docker Compose stack
make stop     # Stop all services
make test     # Run tests
make build    # Compile project
make dev      # Run with local profile
make logs     # Follow service logs
```

## Conventions
- Follow standard Spring Boot patterns (Controller → Service → Repository)
- Use constructor injection over field injection
- JPA entities in `model/` package
- REST controllers return ResponseEntity
- Use `@Valid` for request validation
- Configuration via application.properties with profile overrides
